'''Dentristus''' was a farm hand who was in love with the his [[unnamed lord|lord]]'s daughter, [[Arastasia]], though he knew he would never win her hand.{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=His lord had a beautiful daughter, Arastasia, with whom he was in love, but always he knew he would never win her hand.}} During a harsh winter, the [[Wintertodt]] was drawn from the north devouring animals and crops,{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=That winter was the Great Winter which drew down the Wintertodt from the north, It proceeded to devour the animals upon the farm and freezing the next year's crops.}} devasting villages along its path.{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=From devastated village to devastated village he travelled following the carnage of the Wintertodt.|name=Wintertodt}} He vowed to stop the Wintertodt, for he could not bear to see Arastasia in despair.{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=I cannot bear to see you beautiful daughter cry so over the despair that this beast has caused.}} The lord offered Arastasia's hand in marriage if he were to be successful.{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=if you succeed I will grant you my daughter's hand in marriage}}

Geared with his lord's best armour and weapon,{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=Dressed in the Lord's best armour and wielding his most dangerous weapon Destristus started upon his quest.}} he followed the trail of destruction that the [[Wintertodt]] had left behind. Destrius lay dead before he ever saw the wintertodt, frozen to the bone.{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=Dentristus lay dead before he even saw the Wintertodt, the icy wind freezing him to the bone before he could lay a blow.}} A grim reminder the Wintertodt could not be fought alone.

